title: Total assets of Royal Bank of Canada 2014 to 2019
yAxis: Total assets in billion Canadian dollars
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Total assets in billion Canadian dollars, containing a total of 6 data points.
In general Total assets in billion Canadian dollars has rose over the Year.
Total assets in billion Canadian dollars is slightly increasing from 2014 to 2015, roughly constant from 2015 to 2017, and lastly slightly increasing from 2017 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2014 and 2015.
The highest Total assets in billion Canadian dollars, of value 1428.94 was reached at Year 2019
The lowest Total assets in billion Canadian dollars, of value 940.55 was reported at Year 2014
